  "text": "Remark 3.2. We have shown that the complex structure induced by the quaternion-Kähler moment map, in quaternionic Feix-Kaledin construction corresponds to subbundles of the bundles V 1,0 and V 0,1 defined as annihilators of the parallel sections for ∇ c along the leaves of the (1, 0) and (0, 1)-foliations on S c respectively. It is straight forward to see that through quaternionic Feix-Kaledin construction, we always obtain in this way a complex structure, provided that the c-projective structure is generated by a real-analytic connection with curvature of type (1, 1): in this case any such a connection in the c-projective class equip M with a complex quaternionic structure. Such manifolds have been studied recently by N. Hitchin [CITATION_1] .",
